text: There goes their productivity.
MAILBOX OF THE DAY

> Hi! I’m an avid EDH player, and I see a lot of problems with the site. Its great, but definitely not 100% accurate. A human touch would be nice, instead of computer generated lists. For example:
> A new Edh player would look at your top 100 lands list for their trostani deck, and they would see that Blossoming Sands, the gw lifeland, would be a better choice than savannah. Now, if your an edh player, you know this is definitely not true. This list is either looking at budget decks or something, because there is no way that the GW lifeland is played more than savannah. The other 9 original duals aren’t even on the list! Someone who knows more about magic than a computer should be editing these lists to actually use the top 100 most played lands, instead of playing guildgates and lifelands over true duals. The decks registered on tappedout that you reference are certainly suboptimal, and so maybe you should look at better decks and more competitive decks than recommending new and old edh players to make bad plays.
Yeah Don - stop looking at all those 'trash' decks.
Do your job
i should spend my time editing the 750 commanders
i hope this guy is 11 years old
He's just a kid at heart.
I emailed separately to ask if he wanted to write some articles for us
NOOOOOOOOOO!
"Your list of the top 100 most frequently played cards of a certain type shouldn't reflect how frequently those cards are played."

"There's no way this eleven cent card that has been in the last couple of sets and can be found at the end of any table after a draft for free is more freqently played than this $80 dollar reserve list card that hasn't been printed since 1994."
He wants Alt-Fact EDHREC.
I mean, I get what he wants, but that's not what the site does. I don't get mad McDonalds doesn't sell wrenches.
What he wants exists
Every commander within reason has a primer out there
McWrenches?
He's going to be disappointed when the ai i'm working on at my day job takes his jerb
You're working on an internet troll AI?
No but thats a good one
We elected one so I think that ship sailed.

On a super tangential note, I bought a collection last night from two brothers who I'm fairly sure were straight-up on meth. The broken baby stroller outside filled with cigarette butts was probably the most bleakly symbolic thing I've ever seen in my life
How did you find them? Crack's List?
Nice
He gave them meth for the cards
Thats how
lol, yeah Craig's List. They were yelling at each other the whole time, it was legit a Breaking Bad scene.
Anything good in the collection?

It was super weird. Not a single rare in any of the boxes, but pulled a playset of Mishra's Baubles, six Aether Vials, 6-7 Tops, playset of Counterbalances, double figures of dollar stuff like Rancor and Ghost Quarter, etc. Paid 100, pulled everything I wanted, sold the bulk to my local store for $30 and will probably ebay a Vial or two to get my money back. And I didn't get stabbed.
Beware of papercuts...cards are probably riddled with meth.
I actually put on gloves when I was opening the stuff, not to protect the cards, either, just because I was sure I was gonna get hep c or something
That's fun. I was talking to a guy the other day who could swear he was going to sell his stuff for $.10/common, quarters on uncommon etc to a store.
I think I got $3 per 1000
Which is terrible, but I don't wanna store it all. Sems like a good way to get bed bugs
Yea. Hard pass on that
I offered the dude $3/k and $.10 on bulk rares and he said he can get more online, so I gave his scg and CFB's buylist sites which I was beating. It was a fun exchange
At some point the amount of time you spend sorting and storing all that chaff makes it cost prohibitive to give any more than that

Yep. I didn't press the issue, I just told him what my offer on his bulk(which it mostly was) and I'd make an offer based on the other money cards from there and left it at that. I offered to come by and look through it more if he decided to change his mind and called it good.
I love the collections where guys catalog and price every rare down to bulk rares and have foil Daze in their "bulk"
That wasn't far off actually. In his pictures he had a bunch of theros hydras with $1/$1.50 tags on the sleeves.
Here are all my bindered commons from Darksteel, and this bulk box with a foil Mother of Runes.
Those are the people that I want to send pictures of nm TCG prices to just for a reality check. But I'm too lazy to go through that kind of effort
My favorite was the guy who put random cards behind other cards in his binder. I gave him what I thought was a fair price and he had Nyxathid with a Grim Tutor behind it
I just tell people to call me in a week when no one else offered them anywhere near what I was paying
Yep. That's where I left it with my guy from yesterday
Somewhere along the line the guy dropped the "I have the stock to open a store, so I should be able to charge like a store" line. Ok...
Is goldfish down for anyone else btw?
Yup - it's down
Yeah, tried AT&T internet in WI and TimeWarner in Ohio, down through both
Goldfish is back up
Is there an enchantment that gives everything on the board flying? Not just your stuff
Levitation is just your stuff right?
Gravity Sphere and Mystic Decree remove from all but I'm not seeing a flying equivalent of Concordant Crossroads or Mass Hysteria
Thinking on janky things to do with sandwurm converg.
Ah.
Like Assault Suit + Archetype of imagination.
That'd definitely work.
Thinking of a Warmonger K&T build
There's a lot of one-off instants that give flying, or repeatable stuff like Predator Flagship, Arnjlot's Ascent, Chariot of the Sun, Flying Carpet, Power Matrix, Sailmonger, Skygames
All that stuff feels really dire though, where as a flying Mass Hysteria would be so much cleaner
Another option is to slap flying on new Odric and then assault suit.
Does anyone have any experience with Quiet Speculation's ION card scanner and backend?
I'll have time this summer to catalogue my collection and decks so I'm looking for management tools.
I would assume it is OK. I am not associated with QS anymore but still use Trader Tools
So Trader Tools is purely online.
Yeah. I don't know anything about the scanner but I assume it's good tech
I like the speed they show in the videos, so I'd be willing to pay for a couple of months to plow through my collection.
I just need to better understand where the data lives.
Qs servers, I think
Hrm...I'd want it in a local DB that I control vs solely on their servers.

I think you can type in the url bar firstcard-secondcard
Its the routing thats broke

I think I need to get my lighting set right and not try it against a white table.
I set up my phone about 6-8 inches off the table by stacking a deck box and something to get it in one place, that helped a ton

fair enough
